/'******************************************************************************
**      Inheritance logic
 *****************************************************************************'/
 start
 '':<img:ChipElmos52042.JPG>;
 : Pin **OUT** (5V, 3,3V ) Mode usage;
 note right
     <img:../pictures/chipElmos52042.JPG>
     Configure usage via MODECONF.OUTMODE=[0:1] in <<timeWindow>> after restart:
     <img:../pictures/chipEmlose52042_powerUp.JPG>
  end note

 fork
     :**SIO** Mode: serial write and read and
     configuration using Mencaster code;
     note
         o  Each byte starts and ends by a bit which is always '1' and '0'.
         o  The SIO uses the Manchester Code (biphase-L, falling edge == 1)
            with a baud rate of DATABAUDRATE.
            <img:../pictures/menchesterCode.JPG>
         o  Note: If the LSB is a 0, the SIO line must be driven to 0V actively!
         o  write commands are always 4 to 16 bit long
     end note
     :ljjjj;
 fork again
    :**Digital OUT** Mode: sending data __out analoge__;
 fork again
    :**SENT** Protocol Mode: sendig data __out digital__;
 fork again
    :**Diagnostic**: Output depends anloge (low OUT) or digital (detailed) mode;
 end fork
 stop






'note "A single note" as N1

'note as N1
'    This note is note
'end note
'


